Definition.WordDefinition: Anal \A"nal\, a. [From {Anus}.] (Anat.) Pertaining to, or situated near, the anus; as, the anal fin or glands. [1913 Webster]

anal adj 1: of or related to the anus; "anal thermometer" 2: a stage in psychosexual development when the child's interest is concentrated on the anal region; fixation at this stage is said to result in orderliness, meanness, stubbornness, compulsiveness, etc. [ant: {oral}]
